-- в”Ђв”Ђ Arize AI в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Arize AI is an ML and LLM observability platform that helps teams monitor, evaluate, and debug model and AI agent performance in production.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (AX Free); Pro from $50/month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2020, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$approx 150-200 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Berkeley, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Arize AI 2026: ML and LLM Observability Platform Pricing$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Arize AI offers ML and LLM observability with tracing, evals, and drift detection. Compare its free Phoenix open source tool and AX Pro pricing for 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Arize AI is an artificial intelligence observability and evaluation company founded in January 2020 by Aparna Dhinakaran and Jason Lopatecki and headquartered in Berkeley, California. The company builds tools that help machine learning and AI engineering teams understand, troubleshoot, and improve the performance of models and AI applications running in production. Arize started as a traditional ML monitoring platform focused on drift detection, feature-level analysis, and model performance dashboards, then expanded significantly into large language model and AI agent observability as generative AI adoption grew. Arize has raised a total of roughly 131 million dollars across four funding rounds, including a 38 million dollar Series B led by TCV in September 2022 and a 70 million dollar Series C led by Adams Street Partners, with additional participation from investors including Microsoft's M12 venture fund, Sinewave Ventures, OMERS Ventures, Datadog, PagerDuty, Industry Ventures, and Archerman Capital. The company's flagship commercial product is Arize AX, an enterprise-grade platform offering session-level and span-level tracing of LLM and agent workflows, LLM-as-a-judge automated evaluations, real-time alerting integrated with tools like PagerDuty and Slack, dataset and drift monitoring, and an AI debugging assistant called Alyx that helps engineers diagnose issues faster. Alongside AX, Arize also maintains Phoenix, a fully open-source AI observability and tracing tool launched in 2023 that can be self-hosted with no usage caps and has surpassed two million monthly downloads, making it one of the more widely adopted open-source LLM observability tools. Commercially, Arize follows a freemium model: Phoenix is free and open source, AX Free is a free managed cloud tier with 25,000 spans per month, 1 GB of ingestion, 15-day data retention, and access to Alyx and online evaluations; AX Pro costs 50 dollars per month for 50,000 spans, 10 GB ingestion, and 30-day retention, with additional spans billed at 10 dollars per million and additional storage at 3 dollars per gigabyte; and AX Enterprise offers custom SaaS or self-hosted pricing with configurable retention, dedicated support, uptime SLAs, SOC 2 and HIPAA compliance, SSO enforcement, and role-based access control, with median enterprise contracts reported around 60,000 dollars per year. Arize's target customers are ML engineering teams, AI platform teams, and enterprises building and operating LLM and AI agent applications in production who need visibility into model quality, drift, latency, and failure modes. It competes with other ML and LLM observability vendors such as WhyLabs, Fiddler AI, Galileo, and increasingly with observability features built into broader AI platforms.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '9a7e8122-3695-461f-84e4-19dc93e5180d';

